1
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:52,520
Are you ready?

2
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:53,920
Always.

3
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:56,440
Whatever happens, happens.

4
00:00:56,520 --> 00:00:59,240
PREVIOUSLY

5
00:00:59,320 --> 00:01:02,400
<i>Bass! No, Bass!</i>

6
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:04,640
Bass! Bass!

7
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:09,040
Exchange your life for hers,

8
00:01:09,120 --> 00:01:13,320
<i>so you can take my place on this train.</i>

9
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:29,400
- Hey, guys, look at this!
- What is it?

10
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:30,960
- What?
- He replied.

11
00:01:31,040 --> 00:01:32,360
Wait, what? Let me see.

12
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:34,160
No way, seriously?

13
00:01:34,240 --> 00:01:35,200
What is it?

14
00:01:42,520 --> 00:01:44,160
Uh, you're…

15
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:45,960
Hi, guys.

16
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:48,280
- Hello.
- I've been following you

17
00:01:48,360 --> 00:01:49,280
on social media.

18
00:01:49,360 --> 00:01:52,040
I really like how you play.

19
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:54,920
I'd like to invite your band
to perform at my concert.

20
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:57,080
Would you be interested?

21
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:58,000
Yes, absolutely.

22
00:01:58,080 --> 00:01:59,320
- Of course.
- Are you serious?

23
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,240
Yes.

24
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:02,880
So, what should we prepare?

25
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:04,680
Yeah, what do we need to do?

26
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:07,520
We're preparing
for a big concert right now.

27
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:10,320
It'll probably take
about three to four months

28
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:11,520
before the real show.

29
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,200
Don't worry.

30
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:16,040
You've got time. Can I get your number?

31
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:16,800
- You go.
- Take mine.

32
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:18,000
- Alright.
- Here you go.

33
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:21,360
"I've got the concert date confirmed."

34
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:24,640
"Please block the rehearsal days
I sent earlier."

35
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:26,480
"The venue and time

36
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:27,920
will be confirmed soon."

37
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:33,760
That means we should celebrate!

38
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:36,160
- Let's celebrate!
- Celebrate, hell yeah!

39
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:39,480
So, are we going to play Alice's song?

40
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:41,120
- Of course.
- What do you say, Alice?

41
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:44,000
Alice?

42
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:45,760
Uh.

43
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,800
- She was just here a minute ago.
- Oh.

44
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:52,360
Maybe we got too excited?

45
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:55,160
I'll go find her.

46
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:57,120
Do you know where she went?

47
00:03:08,120 --> 00:03:09,120
Alice.

48
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:13,240
So many things have happened to us, right?

49
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:18,480
But I kind of regret

50
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:23,000
that I only just made up with Mom,

51
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:27,880
just got real friends,

52
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:30,400
and just got to play music again.

53
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,120
Guess my time's almost up.

54
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,120
That's exactly

55
00:04:01,920 --> 00:04:03,880
why we should make the most of it, Alice.

56
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:07,640
Come on.

57
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:10,160
- Where to?
- Just come with me.

58
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:25,160
Excuse me,
please don't run in the hospital.

59
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,520
- Can you just keep playing?
- Sure.

60
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:59,040
I think that verse…

61
00:04:59,120 --> 00:04:59,960
Mhm.

62
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:02,880
Let's try this. Let's say

63
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:04,840
if I do this…

64
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,320
Mm.

65
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:13,080
<i>Even if this is the last time</i>

66
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:18,360
<i>Before my dreams all fade away</i>

67
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:24,480
<i>Please hold my hand</i>

68
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:27,400
<i>Be the one</i>

69
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:30,880
<i>Who pulls me free</i>

70
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:38,160
<i>From this nightmare</i>

71
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,680
<i>I'm trapped inside</i>

72
00:05:58,200 --> 00:06:01,200
<i>The things I must face</i>

73
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:05,400
<i>The things I must endure</i>

74
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:10,680
<i>The darkness that devours my heart</i>

75
00:06:10,760 --> 00:06:13,400
<i>How do I run?</i>

76
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:17,240
<i>Which way to go when there's no light?</i>

77
00:06:17,840 --> 00:06:19,120
Hey.

78
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:21,040
That actually works.

79
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,840
Once I played it, it just clicked.

80
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:26,280
Yeah, I felt that too.

81
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:29,160
When it was only lyrics,
I couldn't picture it.

82
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:30,080
But when you sang,

83
00:06:30,680 --> 00:06:32,120
wow, it's perfect.

84
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:38,040
- Mm.
- So how can I finish writing it?

85
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:41,040
I think

86
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,720
maybe you haven't finished it

87
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:45,760
because you've been too hard on yourself.

88
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:49,440
Try to relax a bit.

89
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:52,920
Once you loosen up,

90
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,640
- the rest will come naturally.
- Wow.

91
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,680
That's easy for you to say.

92
00:06:56,760 --> 00:06:59,400
If it were me, I'd be stuck too.

93
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:05,600
Maybe you should take Alice out to relax.

94
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:10,960
This is already relaxing,
being with you guys.

95
00:07:11,640 --> 00:07:12,920
Look.

96
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,200
Just take a break for a bit.

97
00:07:14,280 --> 00:07:16,240
If you're stuck,
go walk around Chula Park,

98
00:07:16,840 --> 00:07:18,560
enjoy the trees and the birds.

99
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:20,120
Then keep writing there.

100
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:24,720
We'll wait here for the rest of the song.

101
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:28,440
You've got two hours to finish it.
That's your deadline.

102
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:30,560
Well, what are you waiting for?

103
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:31,480
- Go.
- Give it to me.

104
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:32,800
- Come on.
- Okay.

105
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:35,400
Let's go, Alice.

106
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:42,960
Alice, look. The sky's so beautiful.

107
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:46,120
Yeah, it really is.

108
00:07:47,760 --> 00:07:49,640
It's nice coming here.

109
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:51,760
I probably won't get to come again.

110
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:54,400
Every time I walk here,

111
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,000
I'll walk here

112
00:07:57,600 --> 00:07:59,160
like you're still with me,

113
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:01,800
- like you're still right beside me.
- Stop.

114
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:04,800
Enough. I can't listen anymore.

115
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:07,680
Why? It's true.

116
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:11,680
Even if we haven't
been together that long,

117
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:14,360
it feels like forever, Alice.

118
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:18,920
Yeah.

119
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,640
It really does.

120
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,800
For me,

121
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,920
no matter what happens,

122
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:30,240
I'll always feel the same about you.

123
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,480
Feel what?

124
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:37,679
Feel…

125
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:44,240
love.

126
00:08:58,560 --> 00:08:59,480
Alice.

127
00:09:03,920 --> 00:09:06,840
Oh wow, you could write it now?

128
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:09,680
Hm.

129
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:13,280
But I didn't bring my guitar.
Should I go back and get it?

130
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:14,240
No need.

131
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:17,840
It's almost done. But…

132
00:09:17,920 --> 00:09:21,120
I can't figure out the last verse.

133
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:23,520
The last verse?

134
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:29,360
I got it.

135
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,520
- You got it?
- Mm.

136
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:33,200
- What is it?
- Don't peek.

137
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:34,880
- I can't look?
- No.

138
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:36,640
Give it to me.

139
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:42,320
Done.

140
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:44,560
- I…
- Stop.

141
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:46,680
- No peeking. Close it.
- Okay, okay.

142
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:48,240
Hm?

143
00:09:48,760 --> 00:09:49,880
Oh.

144
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:51,400
Hey, it's been over two hours.

145
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:52,920
- Oh yeah…
- Shall we head back?

146
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:53,840
Mm.

147
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,080
Punn.

148
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:17,120
- Yeah?
- Well…

149
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:18,960
I just wanted to say

150
00:10:19,800 --> 00:10:24,760
thank you for everything.

151
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:29,520
Thanks for always supporting me,
for always caring.

152
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,760
It's okay, Alice.

153
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:35,680
I should be the one thanking you.

154
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:40,360
Thank you for letting me find happiness

155
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,040
in doing all this for you.

156
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:46,440
Mm.

157
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,000
Let's go.

158
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:58,920
<i>Even if this is the last time</i>

159
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:02,280
<i>Before my dreams all fade away</i>

160
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:07,880
<i>Please hold my hand</i>

161
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:11,840
<i>Be the one to pull me through</i>

162
00:11:11,920 --> 00:11:16,280
<i>On this final journey</i>

163
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:19,960
<i>So those dreams won't fade away</i>

164
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:25,560
<i>Hold my hand tight</i>

165
00:11:25,640 --> 00:11:29,720
<i>Until we reach our dream</i>
<i>Until we finally make it there</i>

166
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:35,800
<i>Until we're out of this nightmare</i>

167
00:11:43,520 --> 00:11:44,960
- That's fire.
- Whoa.

168
00:11:45,840 --> 00:11:47,440
- So fire.
- Yeah.

169
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:48,880
Alright, everyone.

170
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:52,080
Let me name this song.

171
00:11:53,160 --> 00:11:54,920
I'll name it…

172
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,800
Wow.

173
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:02,040
It's the last nightmare.

174
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,280
From now on,
there'll only be good dreams, Alice.

175
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,080
So cheesy. Oh my god.

176
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:10,000
Hey.

177
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:14,160
Hey, that means we finally
have our own official band song.

178
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:17,520
Let's go!

179
00:12:37,440 --> 00:12:38,280
Alice.

180
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:43,680
I was looking for you.

181
00:12:43,760 --> 00:12:46,200
Hey, we're going out to eat.

182
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:47,120
Mm.

183
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,320
Oh…

184
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:52,440
Are you okay?

185
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,320
Yeah, I'm fine.

186
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:57,680
You guys go ahead.

187
00:12:57,760 --> 00:13:00,000
I think I'll go see my mom.

188
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:04,000
There's not much time left.

189
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:08,280
Then come back

190
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:10,680
when you're done, okay?

191
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:12,400
Mm.

192
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:15,400
Go ahead.

193
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:33,360
Mom, what's wrong?

194
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:35,880
Why are you lying here?

195
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:39,760
Mom. Mom.

196
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,480
Alice?

197
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:44,560
Alice.

198
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:50,480
Alice.

199
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:53,720
Alice.

200
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:57,560
Alice.

201
00:14:08,040 --> 00:14:10,600
Come stay home sometime, okay, sweetie?

202
00:14:22,760 --> 00:14:26,600
<i>Even if this is the last time</i>

203
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:32,120
<i>Before my dreams all fade away</i>

204
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:38,360
<i>Please hold my hand</i>

205
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:43,920
<i>Be the one who pulls me free</i>

206
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:52,120
<i>From this nightmare</i>

207
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:57,040
<i>I'm trapped inside</i>

208
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:12,280
Hey, Punn.

209
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:14,680
Is Alice here yet?

210
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:16,560
Yeah.

211
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:22,720
Hey, Alice.

212
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:24,600
Hey. Hello.

213
00:15:25,720 --> 00:15:27,080
How are you?

214
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:33,520
Today's the last day, isn't it?

215
00:15:42,560 --> 00:15:46,960
<i>Even if this is the last time</i>

216
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:50,320
<i>Before my dreams all fade away</i>

217
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:56,040
<i>Please hold my hand</i>

218
00:15:56,120 --> 00:16:00,480
<i>Be the one to pull me through</i>

219
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:04,880
<i>On this final journey</i>

220
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:07,720
<i>So those dreams won't fade away</i>

221
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:12,960
Alice!

222
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:23,840
Alice's gone.

223
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:39,440
Alice.

224
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:42,920
How is she doing?

225
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:45,720
Her condition's worsening.

226
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:48,920
She's been declining rapidly.

227
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,680
The hospital already called her mother.

228
00:16:52,760 --> 00:16:54,080
She should be on her way.

229
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:57,840
Has there been no improvement at all?

230
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:01,760
Please excuse me.

231
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:10,280
Alice.

232
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:17,040
I thought you'd come back.

233
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:21,200
Where did you go, Alice?

234
00:17:23,520 --> 00:17:25,440
Are you really not coming back this time?

235
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:29,920
Why did he make that offer?

236
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:32,240
Why?

237
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:43,520
Where would she go?

238
00:17:51,120 --> 00:17:52,040
Alice.

239
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:54,800
Alice, are you there?

240
00:17:57,240 --> 00:17:58,160
Alice.

241
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:00,600
Can you hear me?

242
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:10,160
Alice.

243
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:28,800
Punn.

244
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:31,800
Aren't you eating?

245
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:33,880
Eat up.

246
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:37,200
Yeah.

247
00:18:46,120 --> 00:18:47,440
Um, and…

248
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:18,160
Good evening, ma'am.

249
00:19:19,520 --> 00:19:20,520
Hello.

250
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:24,880
Thank you for visiting Alice so often.

251
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,000
It's no problem.

252
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:29,800
Actually,

253
00:19:32,040 --> 00:19:34,000
I feel so guilty.

254
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:40,520
I never imagined
I'd have so little time with her.

255
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:44,080
If I had another chance,

256
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:49,560
I'd be the best mother I could be.

257
00:19:51,720 --> 00:19:54,080
I'd listen more.

258
00:19:54,640 --> 00:19:57,400
I'd try harder to understand her.

259
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:01,080
I'd care more about her feelings.

260
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:09,040
But before this…

261
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:14,440
I was a terrible mother.

262
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:16,560
I only ever thought about myself.

263
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:20,440
I forced her to do
what she didn't want to.

264
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:24,120
And I didn't even know
if she really wanted to be a doctor.

265
00:20:35,720 --> 00:20:37,160
It broke my heart.

266
00:20:42,360 --> 00:20:44,280
I'm so sorry, my girl.

267
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:47,560
Ma'am.

268
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:51,160
Not sure if you'll believe me,

269
00:20:52,840 --> 00:20:55,400
but I had a chance to see Alice.

270
00:20:59,120 --> 00:21:00,480
What do you mean?

271
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:06,040
Alice told me

272
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:10,600
she knows how much you love her.

273
00:21:12,480 --> 00:21:14,760
If she could come back,

274
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:18,040
she'd do everything for you.

275
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:21,720
Whatever you wanted,
she said she'd give her very best.

276
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:29,760
Excuse me.

277
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:38,800
Ma'am.

278
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:45,760
Her vitals are dropping fast.

279
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:47,760
