make sure everyone's on time.

506
00:37:11,120 --> 00:37:12,520
- What's up, Punn? You okay?
- What's wrong?

507
00:37:12,600 --> 00:37:13,640
Maybe too much talking, he's sleepy.

508
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:16,480
- Are you alright?
- I…

509
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:19,240
- What?
- I think I'm just a bit tired.

510
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:20,200
Hm?

511
00:37:20,280 --> 00:37:21,280
Huh?

512
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:22,760
Let me take a nap.

513
00:37:22,840 --> 00:37:24,040
- He's old.
- Yeah.

514
00:37:24,120 --> 00:37:25,520
Yeah, go nap.

515
00:37:26,040 --> 00:37:27,960
- Deep sleep.
- No waking up.

516
00:37:28,040 --> 00:37:29,360
No running away.

517
00:37:30,360 --> 00:37:31,360
Whoa.

518
00:37:34,480 --> 00:37:39,440
Get some rest.
When we're done, I'll wake you up.

519
00:37:45,720 --> 00:37:47,960
I already gave you a chance.

520
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:51,560
But you chose your own path.

521
00:37:52,840 --> 00:37:55,200
Now you must face the consequences.

522
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:57,560
Hm, no…

523
00:37:58,960 --> 00:38:02,640
There must be a way to fix this.
What can I do?

524
00:38:03,440 --> 00:38:04,440
Fix it?

525
00:38:06,760 --> 00:38:10,600
Do you think getting a second chance
is that easy?

526
00:38:11,880 --> 00:38:13,560
I don't mean it like that, but…

527
00:38:14,080 --> 00:38:16,280
I couldn't let Alice die.

528
00:38:17,640 --> 00:38:19,440
Haven't you ever wanted
to protect someone you love?

529
00:38:19,520 --> 00:38:20,640
- You--
- Enough!

530
00:38:22,600 --> 00:38:24,160
Who do you think you are

531
00:38:24,800 --> 00:38:27,240
to talk about me like that?

532
00:38:28,200 --> 00:38:29,600
What if I agree to trade?

533
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:32,680
You once told me

534
00:38:34,640 --> 00:38:36,360
that if I trade my life

535
00:38:37,240 --> 00:38:38,760
and become a reaper instead of you,

536
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:44,280
Alice will live. Right?

537
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:47,040
Are you sure

538
00:38:48,320 --> 00:38:50,040
you want to make that decision?

539
00:38:50,640 --> 00:38:51,640
I'm sure.

540
00:38:53,240 --> 00:38:55,520
If it means Alice gets to live,

541
00:38:56,520 --> 00:38:57,960
I'll do anything.

542
00:39:02,360 --> 00:39:03,240
But…

543
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:08,080
can I ask one last thing?

544
00:39:10,120 --> 00:39:11,000
What is it?

545
00:39:12,840 --> 00:39:14,840
Let me perform
